bility for overall medical management of each patient. Allow residents an extensive surgical experience. OB/Gyn Department Faculty For more information, please contact: Tim Durkee, MD, PhD Chair, Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology (815) 971-6374 Departments Academic Departments Biomedical Sciences Directory Biomedical Sciences Adjunct Faculty Biomedical Research Faculty Regenerative Medicine and Disability Research Laboratory Research People Publications Useful Links News Contacts Biomedical Sciences Summer Programs SMART Program Family and Community Medicine Family Medicine Clerkship Medicine and Medical Specialties Medicine Clerkship Obstetrics and Gynecology OB/Gyn Faculty Pathology Pathology Medical Education Pathology Clerkship Pediatrics MERIT Ways to Help MERIT Psychiatry Teaching Activities Surgery and Surgical Specialties Centers About  Education  Research  Patient Care  Departments  News  Giving INFORMATION FOR: Prospective and Current Students  Faculty & Staff  Alumni & Friends  Patients  Businesses and Community RESOURCES: UIC Directory  Blackboard  Emergency Information  Contact Us  Apply Now  Give  Contact Us Connect with us!    If you have questions, comments, or problems accessing this site, please E-mail the webmaster  © Copyright 2019 University of Illinois College of Medicine   | Privacy Statement College of Medicine | Chicago | Peoria | Rockford | Urbana                                                                                                                                               